Two loves I have, of comfort and despair,
That like two spirits do suggest me still.
My better angel is a man right fair,
With his short gentle breast adorned with jewels,
And having no fear of sight in me to show,
Who may find his love in my heart,
Or say his kisses to me when his lips are more sad.
But I shall bear him,
If his love make his leave more ill-chosen.
